<div class="no-gutter row">
    <div class="col-md-10 col-md-offset-1">
        <div id="faq_main" class="panel">
            <div class="panel-heading" style="background-color:#111;color:#fff;">
                <h1>FAQ Advising Questions</h1>
            </div>
            <div class="main panel-body">
                <div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel panel-heading">
                            <h4>Where can I find my degree requirements?</h4>
                        </div>
                        <div class="answer-body">
                            The <%= link_to 'University Bulletin', 'http://bulletin.case.edu/' %>
                            is your legally binding list of requirements. You alone are
                            <%= link_to 'responsible', 'http://case.edu/ugstudies/academic-policies/academic-regulations/' %>
                            for making sure they are correct by the time of your graduation.
                            SIS is not guaranteed to be up-to-date or error-free.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel panel-heading">
                            <h4>What if the requirements have changed since I entered CWRU?</h4>
                        </div>
                        <div class="answer-body">
                            Your official requirements are the ones that were instated when
                            you matriculated. Some departments may have allow you to switch
                            to a later set of requirements, but you'll need to check with
                            your advisor first.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel panel-heading">
                            <h4>What if what I see on SIS doesn't match up with what I see on the Bulletin?</h4>
                        </div>
                        <div class="answer-body">
                            Please keep in mind that if the change is in your favor, you may
                            need to fill out an advisement correction form. All Undergraduate
                            Studies forms are available in their office and online
                            <%= link_to 'here', 'http://case.edu/ugstudies/forms/' %>.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel panel-heading">
                            <h4>What should I do if I can't reach my advisor?</h4>
                        </div>
                        <div class="answer-body">
                            Remember your advisors are human, too, so give them an
                            appropriate amount of time to respond. If emailing and showing
                            up to office hours aren't enough or if it's a time-sensitive
                            issue, you can always talk to your Undergraduate Studies Dean
                            during
                            <%= link_to 'Walk-In Hours', 'http://case.edu/ugstudies/walkin/' %>
                            for official business (major changes, hold releases, requirement
                            conflicts, etc.). Office hours change every week to make sure you
                            can find a time that doesn't conflict with your classes.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel panel-heading">
                            <h4>How do I know who my Dean is?</h4>
                        </div>
                        <div class="answer-body">
                            You can check your Dean
                            <%= link_to 'here', 'http://case.edu/ugstudies/about-us/who-we-are/' %>.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel panel-heading">
                            <h4>Is X number of credits too many?</h4>
                        </div>
                        <div class="answer-body">
                            You're the only one who can judge how many credits you can
                            handle. 12 is the minimum amount of credits to remain a full-time
                            student. Don't compare yourself to others to determine how many
                            credits you can handle in a single semester. Gather your own
                            information on the courses you're considering and consider your
                            own limits to make your own judgement.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel panel-heading">
                            <h4>
                                A class I've been waiting to take hasn't been offered in a while.
                                When will it be offered again?
                            </h4>
                        </div>
                        <div class="answer-body">
                            We can't predict when classes will be offered again, but you can
                            sign up to be notified via email with The Jolly Advisor
                            <%= link_to 'wishlist', wishlist_path %> feature. Additionally, use
                            Course Show Pages to see when the class was last offered and
                            which professor taught the course.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel panel-heading">
                            <h4>How up-to-date is The Jolly Advisor?</h4>
                        </div>
                        <div class="answer-body">
                          We pull in new data from SIS every 24 hours, so we're never more
                          than a day behind.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel panel-heading">
                            <h4>What if I find something that's incorrect on this page or on The Jolly Advisor?</h4>
                        </div>
                        <div class="answer-body">
                            We do our best to keep information up-to-date. This is a
                            student-run site, so we can quickly respond to changes or
                            discrepancies. All you have to do is
                            <%= link_to 'let us know', 'http://github.com/hacsoc/the_jolly_advisor/issues/new' %>
                            and we'll get it fixed as soon as possible.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
